title: Jemaine Clement
summary: Jemaine Atea Mahana Clement (born 10 January 1974)[2] is a New Zealand actor, comedian, director, musician, singer and writer. With Bret McKenzie, as the Grammy Award-winning comedy duo Flight of the Conchords, he has released several albums and created comedy series for both the BBC and HBO. For the comedy series, he received six Primetime Emmy nominations.
